data.title: Astrology Birth Chart for Sidney Rand (May. 9, 1916)
data.meta_description: Liz has two passions in life: astrology and relationships. As a professional astrologer, she has been featured in multiple publications such as BestLife, FoxNews, Glam, Glamour, and MindBodyGreen. She shares all her discoveries and observations on this website.
data.text:
Sidney Anders Rand was an American Lutheran minister, educator and college president. He served under the Carter administration as United States Ambassador to Norway from 1980 to 1981.

Sidney Rand was born on May 9, 1916, in Eldred, Pennsylvania, United States. His birth geographical coordinates are 41° 57’ 28” North latitude and 78° 23’ 7” West longitude, with an altitude of 439 meters above sea level. Sidney Rand passed away at the age of 87 in 2003.

Astrologically, Sidney Rand falls under the Sun sign of Taurus, with Leo as his Ascendant, Leo as his Moon sign, and Cancer as his Black Moon Lilith sign.
